21/05/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The government and US representatives on Thursday (May 20th) started negotiating a new agreement on extraditing those accused or convicted of serious crimes. 
The current agreement dates back to 1901. 
US Ambassador to Serbia Mary Warlick said the negotiations exemplify the deepening bilateral relations and present an opportunity to overcome modern threats. 
Justice Ministry State Secretary Slobodan Homen, who is leading Belgrade's delegation at the negotiations, says Serbia has been negotiating similar agreements with Croatia and Italy. 
(B92, RTS, Tanjug, Blic, Beta - 20/05/10)
